Clean data to make the dataset not adjust with large anomaly values

In[5]:
def clean_data(data):
    Q1 = np.percentile(data, 25)
    Q3 = np.percentile(data, 75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5*Q1
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5*Q3
    return data[(data >= lower_bound) & (data <= upper_bound)].reshape(-1,1)

Using KMeans to cluster the data

Find anomaly using Interquartile Range from function clean_data()

In[6]:
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=centers.shape[0], random_state=42) 
kmeans.fit(X) 
kmeans_distances = np.min(kmeans.transform(X), axis=1).reshape(-1,1)
cleaned_distances = clean_data(kmeans_distances)
percentile_90 = np.percentile(cleaned_distances, 90)
anomaly = (kmeans_distances > percentile_90)

In[53]:
def display_cm(y_test, y_pred):
    matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', 
                xticklabels=['Predicted Negative', 'Predicted Positive',], 
                yticklabels=['True Negative', 'True Positive'])
    plt.ylabel('True Anomaly')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Anomaly')
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
    plt.show()

display_cm(y_test, y_pred)
